        <div class="container">
            <header id="header">
                <div class="header-title">
                    <h1><i class="fas fa-monument"></i> Charminar</h1>
                </div><br>
                <div class="header-subcontent">
                    <p>The iconic monument and beating heart of Hyderabad</p>
                    <div class="hyderabad-badge">
                        <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hyderabad, Telangana, India
                    </div>
                </div>
                </header>
        <div class="main-image-container">
            <img src="https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/hyderabadindia-december-16-charminar-hyderabad-600nw-555387298.jpg"
                alt="Charminar" class="main-image">
            <div class="image-overlay">
                <h2>"The Arc de Triomphe of the East"</h2>
                <p>Built in 1591 by Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah</p>
            </div>
        </div>
            </header>
        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> Historical Significance</h2>
            <p>Charminar, meaning "Four Towers", is a magnificent square edifice built with granite and lime mortar.
                This grand architectural marvel stands at the intersection of the historical trade route that connects
                the markets of Golconda with the port city of Machilipatnam.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                The monument was built to commemorate the eradication of plague from Hyderabad. Each of the four arches
                faces a fundamental point and opens into four streets that once led to the royal courts.
            </div>

            <p>The structure is a perfect square, measuring 20 meters on each side, with four grand arches facing the
                cardinal directions. Each minaret soars 56 meters into the Hyderabad skyline and contains a spiral
                staircase with 149 steps leading to the upper floor.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-archway"></i> Architectural
                Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Indo-Islamic architecture with Persian influences</li>
                <li>Four minarets with intricate carvings</li>
                <li>Double gallery at the top offering panoramic views</li>
                <li>Mosque on the top floor - one of the oldest in Hyderabad</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="nearby-section">
            <section class="restaurants" id="restaurants">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Must-Try Hyderabadi Cuisine</h2>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1631515243349-e0cb75fb8d3a?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Paradise Biryani" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-drumstick-bite"></i> Paradise Biryani <span
                            class="hyderabadi-badge">Iconic</span></h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Opposite Charminar Bus Stop</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 11:30 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Hyderabadi Dum Biryani, Mirchi Ka Salan, Double Ka Meetha
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1565557623262-b51c2513a641?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Nimrah Café" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-mug-hot"></i> Nimrah Café & Bakery</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Near Charminar, Bank Street</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 5:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Irani Chai, Osmania Biscuits, Kheema Samosa
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601050690597-df0568f70950?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Pista House Haleem" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-ice-cream"></i> Pista House Haleem</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Near Charminar, Naya Pul</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> Seasonal (Ramadan Special)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Hyderabadi Haleem, Shahi Tukda, Falooda
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQoH2eZ5Eohj5zc8rbwcLDkOY66pKi5rQu7nQ&s"
                            alt="Shah Ghouse Café" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Shah Ghouse Café</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Near Charminar, Madina Circle</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 5:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Mutton Kheema, Chicken 65, Badam Milk
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/0/92020/f7b6a9e4cb7676fb7e8e320d8289be74.jpg?output-format=webp&fit=around|300:273&crop=300:273;,"
                            alt="Grand Hotel" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-hotel"></i> Grand Hotel - Kebabs & Curries</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Abids, 2 km from Charminar</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Boti Kebabs, Mutton Dalcha, Hyderabadi Bagara Rice
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="famous-places" id="attractions">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> Nearby Attractions</h2>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://i0.wp.com/pixahive.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Laad-Bazar-in-Hyderabad-93828-pixahive.jpg?fit=2560%2C1440&ssl=1"
                            alt="Laad Bazaar" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-shopping-bag"></i> Laad Bazaar</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> 2 min walk from Charminar</div>
                    <p>Famous for exquisite bangles, pearls, and traditional Hyderabadi attire. The market's colorful
                        lanes are lined with shops selling lacquer bangles since the Qutb Shahi era.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://mrwallpaper.com/images/hd/makkah-hd-madina-masjid-6h6mzikvd5vqvknq.jpg"
                            alt="Mecca Masjid" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-university"></i> Mecca Masjid</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> 5 min walk from Charminar</div>
                    <p>One of India's largest mosques that can accommodate 10,000 worshippers. Built with bricks made
                        from soil brought from Mecca, hence the name.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.alphacoders.com/659/659470.jpg" alt="Chowmahalla Palace"
                            class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-chess-rook"></i> Chowmahalla Palace</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 10 min drive from Charminar</div>
                    <p>The official residence of Nizams of Hyderabad, showcasing the splendor of their rule. The palace
                        complex consists of four palaces in a unique architectural style.</p>
                </div>

